{"id":"277089620_Backstepping-based_robust-adaptive_control_of_a_nonlinear_2-DOF_piezoactuator","abstract":"This paper deals with the control of a two degrees of freedom (2-DOF) piezoelectric actuator for precise positioning and which exhibits strong hysteresis nonlinearity and strong cross-couplings. To tackle the nonlinearity and the cross-couplings, we propose two decoupled models in which they are considered as (fictive) external disturbances which require proper characterization. Then, a backstepping technique is proposed to construct a robust controller that merges sliding-mode and adaptive schemes. Extensive experimental tests are finally carried out to prove the efficiency of the modeling and control technique proposed.","authors":["Juan Escareno","Micky Rakotondrabe","Didace Habineza"],"meta":["August 2015Control Engineering Practice 41","DOI:10.1016/j.conengprac.2015.04.007"],"references":["260330784_Inverse_Rate-Dependent_Prandtl-Ishlinskii_Model_for_Feedforward_Compensation_of_Hysteresis_in_a_Piezomicropositioning_Actuator","257775815_Robotic_Microassembly_and_micromanipulation_at_FEMTO-ST","256195163_The_Atomic_Force_Microscope","245373692_Design_and_Analysis_of_Discrete-Time_Repetitive_Control_for_Scanning_Probe_Microscopes","228714099_Adaptive_set-point_control_of_robotic_manipulators_with_amplitude-limited_control_inputs","228663562_A_Review_of_Feedforward_Control_Approaches_in_Nanopositioning_for_High-Speed_SPM","224717963_Combined_FeedforwardFeedback_Control_of_Atomic_Force_Microscopes","224695428_Plurilinear_Modeling_and_discrete_-Synthesis_Control_of_a_Hysteretic_and_Creeped_Unimorph_Piezoelectric_Cantilever","224605631_Complete_Open_Loop_Control_of_Hysteretic_Creeped_and_Oscillating_Piezoelectric_Cantilevers","224604631_Reducing_Cross-Coupling_in_a_Compliant_XY_Nanopositioner_for_Fast_and_Accurate_Raster_Scanning","224597361_A_New_Method_for_Robust_Damping_and_Tracking_Control_of_Scanning_Probe_Microscope_Positioning_Stages","224557003_Force_est